    leftPage: "Climate change refers to the long-term shift in global temperatures and weather patterns on Earth. While some natural climate change happens slowly over thousands of years, the rapid warming we see today is caused mainly by human activities. Burning fossil fuels like coal, oil, and gas releases carbon dioxide into the atmosphere. This gas traps heat from the sun, causing the planet to warm up — a process called the greenhouse effect.",
