    shortDesc: "How the moon controls Earth's tides and why our oceans regulate the planet's climate.",
    leftPage: "Oceans cover over seventy percent of the Earth's surface and contain ninety seven percent of all the water on our planet. The ocean plays a crucial role in regulating the Earth's climate — it absorbs about a quarter of all carbon dioxide produced by humans, and stores enormous amounts of heat from the sun. Ocean currents act like a global conveyor belt, moving warm and cold water around the planet and controlling temperatures on land.",
